JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South African e-commerce and pay-TV group Naspers will pay R960 million ($69 million) to increase its stake in local online retailer Takealot, the companies said in a joint statement on Tuesday.They did not disclose the size of the stake but Naspers already owns about 40% of Takealot, whose other investor is US investment firm Tiger Global Management.The deal forms part of Naspers&#8217; strategy to invest in internet firms in emerging markets.Its investments include a stake in Tencent Holdings, which has become China&#8217;s largest internet company. Naspers owns about a third of the company.($1 = R13.8875)